1
00:00:00,164 --> 00:00:01,924
A NETFLIX ORIGINAL SERIES

2
00:01:22,837 --> 00:01:27,020
METEOR GARDEN

3
00:01:27,164 --> 00:01:30,084
EPISODE 10

4
00:01:50,244 --> 00:01:52,324
Among these cards,
which has the highest value?

5
00:01:56,684 --> 00:01:58,684
Ace of Diamonds.

6
00:01:58,764 --> 00:01:59,604
Are you sure?

7
00:02:00,244 --> 00:02:01,164
I'm sure.

8
00:02:03,084 --> 00:02:04,004
Hearts...

9
00:02:05,364 --> 00:02:06,724
Jack of Hearts.

10
00:02:10,044 --> 00:02:11,404
Clubs...

11
00:02:13,484 --> 00:02:15,004
King of Clubs.

12
00:02:21,444 --> 00:02:22,564
Diamonds.

13
00:02:24,524 --> 00:02:25,804
Spades...

14
00:02:26,724 --> 00:02:27,964
Queen of Spades.

15
00:02:47,004 --> 00:02:47,884
Am I wrong again?

16
00:02:48,604 --> 00:02:50,484
No, but you're too slow.

17
00:02:51,084 --> 00:02:53,564
Hey, it's quite amazing
that I didn't make a mistake, okay?

18
00:03:00,004 --> 00:03:01,284
I'll do better.

19
00:03:01,924 --> 00:03:03,724
Since you already know the basics,

20
00:03:03,804 --> 00:03:05,364
the biggest problem now

21
00:03:05,444 --> 00:03:07,644
is that you always expose
the cards you have.

22
00:03:08,844 --> 00:03:09,684
No way.

23
00:03:10,404 --> 00:03:11,604
You have a lot of spades.

24
00:03:13,364 --> 00:03:14,644
Am I right?

25
00:03:15,924 --> 00:03:17,764
You're insanely good at this.

26
00:03:17,924 --> 00:03:19,524
Try to bluff and see if you can fool me.

27
00:03:19,804 --> 00:03:21,444
If you can do that,
then we stand a chance.

28
00:03:23,924 --> 00:03:24,764
All right.

29
00:03:26,684 --> 00:03:28,564
Do you like studying at Mingde University?

30
00:03:28,964 --> 00:03:30,044
Yes.

31
00:03:30,484 --> 00:03:32,284
The people here are really amazing.

32
00:03:32,844 --> 00:03:33,884
You don't like it here.

33
00:03:34,604 --> 00:03:36,604
That doesn't count. You already know that.

34
00:03:37,164 --> 00:03:38,404
Do you like Si?

35
00:03:39,324 --> 00:03:40,444
Of course not.

36
00:03:41,044 --> 00:03:42,244
I asked you to fool me.

37
00:03:42,364 --> 00:03:44,724
If you don't like him,
you should have said that you do.

38
00:03:45,284 --> 00:03:46,644
I couldn't make myself say that.

39
00:03:46,724 --> 00:03:48,044
Then do you like me?

40
00:03:53,484 --> 00:03:54,324
No.

41
00:03:55,964 --> 00:03:57,684
That seems like the truth.

42
00:03:57,764 --> 00:03:59,084
That's not true.

43
00:03:59,164 --> 00:04:00,924
I was just kidding.

44
00:04:08,284 --> 00:04:10,244
Who asks questions like that?

45
00:04:10,324 --> 00:04:11,244
How can I answer that?

46
00:04:12,684 --> 00:04:13,764
Only you can't.

47
00:04:15,524 --> 00:04:16,804
Then do you like Jing?

48
00:04:22,404 --> 00:04:23,644
Sorry.

49
00:04:23,884 --> 00:04:25,564
I shouldn't have asked that question.

50
00:04:27,524 --> 00:04:29,564
If I say I'm already over her,
would you believe me?

51
00:04:34,924 --> 00:04:36,684
Do you want me to stay here?

52
00:04:37,684 --> 00:04:38,684
Yes.

53
00:04:39,684 --> 00:04:41,204
Then I'll do my best to stay,

54
00:04:41,844 --> 00:04:43,964
so that I can do everything
to protect you.

55
00:05:20,484 --> 00:05:21,844
If Shancai leaves Mingde,

56
00:05:22,484 --> 00:05:23,444
I'll leave F4.

57
00:05:26,404 --> 00:05:27,684
Do you know what you're saying?

58
00:05:31,684 --> 00:05:34,564
Although it's cool to be a part of F4,

59
00:05:35,244 --> 00:05:38,244
if you bully Shancai, you're my enemy.

60
00:05:39,524 --> 00:05:42,324
Qinghe, you're not that important.

61
00:05:43,484 --> 00:05:45,644
And Shancai doesn't even like you.

62
00:05:46,644 --> 00:05:48,404
That doesn't matter.

63
00:05:48,564 --> 00:05:49,884
I like Shancai.

64
00:05:50,964 --> 00:05:53,204
If I expect the person I like
to like me as well,

65
00:05:53,764 --> 00:05:54,964
that's not manly at all.

66
00:05:58,204 --> 00:05:59,084
Daoming Si.

67
00:05:59,604 --> 00:06:02,364
If you like Shancai,
you have to treat her nicely.

68
00:06:03,444 --> 00:06:04,964
Even if Shancai doesn't like you,

69
00:06:05,684 --> 00:06:07,964
it should be enough for you
to see her happy,

70
00:06:08,364 --> 00:06:09,204
isn't it?

71
00:06:10,484 --> 00:06:14,124
Qinghe, I suddenly realized
that you have the potential to join F4.

72
00:06:15,364 --> 00:06:17,844
What you just said is very manly.

73
00:06:18,404 --> 00:06:19,884
Start practicing how to play Bridge.

74
00:06:20,444 --> 00:06:22,404
This way, if F4 really loses a member,

75
00:06:23,124 --> 00:06:26,804
at least we can have a full team
in competitions.

76
00:06:36,724 --> 00:06:38,884
<i>From the very first day
I entered Mingde University,</i>

77
00:06:39,084 --> 00:06:42,084
<i>I heard about all sorts of bets made
when playing against F4.</i>

78
00:06:42,684 --> 00:06:44,284
<i>I never imagined</i>

79
00:06:44,604 --> 00:06:47,764
<i>I'd receive a joker card
to fight Daoming Si</i>

80
00:06:48,004 --> 00:06:50,604
<i>with Huaze Lei on my side
during my freshman year.</i>

81
00:06:54,724 --> 00:06:56,164
Who do you think will win?

82
00:06:57,284 --> 00:06:59,004
Daoming Si, of course.

83
00:06:59,204 --> 00:07:00,884
Shancai doesn't know how to play Bridge.

84
00:07:00,964 --> 00:07:04,404
Even if Huaze Lei is amazing at it,
she'll be useless.

85
00:07:05,484 --> 00:07:06,364
Shancai.

86
00:07:08,164 --> 00:07:09,564
Do your best. I hope you'll win.

87
00:07:10,764 --> 00:07:11,604
Look.

88
00:07:11,684 --> 00:07:12,924
SHANCAI, YOU CAN DO IT

89
00:07:24,844 --> 00:07:26,124
Did you sleep well last night?

90
00:07:26,204 --> 00:07:28,804
I'm so nervous.
I didn't sleep well at all.

91
00:07:29,844 --> 00:07:30,684
Don't be scared.

92
00:07:34,884 --> 00:07:37,204
Actually, I slept really well.
I fooled you, right?

93
00:07:38,164 --> 00:07:40,284
Yes, you did.
You can make it on your own now.

94
00:07:43,924 --> 00:07:45,524
Then do we stand a chance now?

95
00:07:45,964 --> 00:07:46,804
My gosh!

96
00:07:47,204 --> 00:07:50,204
-Why are they holding hands?
-Right?

97
00:08:05,164 --> 00:08:06,004
Shancai.

98
00:08:06,244 --> 00:08:09,684
Welcome to the Bridge Room and to
the two-on-two competition against the F4.

99
00:08:10,244 --> 00:08:11,924
Did Huaze Lei explain the rules to you?

100
00:08:13,084 --> 00:08:13,924
Yes.

101
00:08:14,004 --> 00:08:16,364
Do you plan to hold hands
while playing Bridge?

102
00:08:19,364 --> 00:08:21,404
Si will play with Meizuo,
and Shancai with Lei.

103
00:08:21,484 --> 00:08:23,124
The two teams will take turns dealing.

104
00:08:23,204 --> 00:08:24,764
Six tricks will be added
to the card they have called.

105
00:08:24,844 --> 00:08:28,084
Win the number you bid or more,
and you win the game. Otherwise, you lose.

106
00:08:28,924 --> 00:08:29,964
Are we clear?

107
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:32,684
Yes.

108
00:08:33,644 --> 00:08:34,604
Please have a seat.

109
00:08:44,124 --> 00:08:45,644
You know what's at stake, right?

110
00:08:48,684 --> 00:08:49,884
Don't we all?

111
00:08:51,724 --> 00:08:52,964
What's at stake here?

112
00:08:54,564 --> 00:08:56,164
Shancai, tell them.

113
00:09:02,684 --> 00:09:03,844
What's at stake

114
00:09:05,364 --> 00:09:06,244
is that if I win,

115
00:09:07,524 --> 00:09:08,604
you have to forgive me.

116
00:09:14,564 --> 00:09:16,124
Is it that important to you?

117
00:09:18,764 --> 00:09:19,604
Yes.

118
00:09:20,124 --> 00:09:21,244
From what I can see,

119
00:09:21,964 --> 00:09:25,044
you just want to be free from guilt
when you're in a relationship with Lei.

120
00:09:26,644 --> 00:09:27,564
Maybe.

121
00:09:28,444 --> 00:09:29,764
Then I definitely refuse to lose.

122
00:09:30,924 --> 00:09:32,124
What if I win?

123
00:09:34,524 --> 00:09:35,924
Then I won't see Shancai again.

124
00:09:41,404 --> 00:09:42,764
You said that on your own accord.

125
00:09:43,524 --> 00:09:45,524
Yes, I did.

126
00:09:46,404 --> 00:09:47,804
But I might not lose.

127
00:09:48,324 --> 00:09:49,324
Right?

128
00:09:50,564 --> 00:09:51,404
Yes.

129
00:09:53,964 --> 00:09:55,564
All right. Let the competition begin.

130
00:10:02,084 --> 00:10:03,044
Please check your cards.

131
00:10:11,364 --> 00:10:13,004
Shancai, you can call your card first.

132
00:10:17,444 --> 00:10:18,684
One of Hearts.

133
00:10:19,524 --> 00:10:20,724
One of Spades.

134
00:10:21,844 --> 00:10:23,084
Three of Hearts.

135
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:24,004
<i>What?</i>

136
00:10:25,084 --> 00:10:27,004
<i>Huaze Lei is calling
the same Hearts suit as me?</i>

137
00:10:27,084 --> 00:10:29,004
I don't have any Hearts cards.

138
00:10:29,084 --> 00:10:31,364
I just bluffed it initially.

139
00:10:34,004 --> 00:10:34,884
Four of Clubs.

140
00:10:35,604 --> 00:10:37,924
<i>Daoming Si is calling four of Clubs now.</i>

141
00:10:38,724 --> 00:10:41,124
<i>If I want to continue calling,
I have to go with four too.</i>

142
00:10:41,204 --> 00:10:44,724
<i>That means I should at least
win ten tricks in order to win.</i>

143
00:10:45,204 --> 00:10:46,884
<i>I only have three Clubs cards.</i>

144
00:10:47,404 --> 00:10:50,204
<i>If Huaze Lei also has them...</i>

145
00:11:01,324 --> 00:11:02,484
The trump suit is Clubs.

146
00:11:02,964 --> 00:11:04,524
Huaze Lei, please proceed.

147
00:11:10,604 --> 00:11:12,804
Shancai, Lei made a mistake.

148
00:11:13,524 --> 00:11:15,244
He thinks that you have the ace of Hearts.

149
00:11:15,764 --> 00:11:17,244
That's why he played the Hearts suit.

150
00:11:17,524 --> 00:11:19,044
He wants you to win the first trick.

151
00:11:19,564 --> 00:11:21,644
Actually, the ace of Hearts is with me.

152
00:11:22,484 --> 00:11:24,644
It looks like your plan
is not going to work.

153
00:11:38,404 --> 00:11:41,324
Shancai has no Hearts. The trump suit,
two of Clubs, wins the first trick.

154
00:11:44,364 --> 00:11:46,364
Shancai, you did great.

155
00:11:50,204 --> 00:11:53,764
I never thought the innocent Shancai
would cheat.

156
00:11:55,604 --> 00:11:57,724
Even if Shancai cheats, she's still cute.

157
00:11:58,364 --> 00:12:01,644
Unlike others who tell the truth,
but always hurts people.

158
00:12:06,324 --> 00:12:08,404
A liar is more despicable, of course.

159
00:12:09,684 --> 00:12:11,004
Aren't you like that?

160
00:12:12,724 --> 00:12:14,764
Please note that this is a Bridge game.

161
00:12:15,324 --> 00:12:16,644
Refrain from verbal attacks.

162
00:12:18,284 --> 00:12:20,484
Shancai, the winner continues playing.

163
00:12:36,604 --> 00:12:38,804
Shancai's ace of Diamonds beats you all.

164
00:12:39,924 --> 00:12:42,764
-She wins the second trick.
-Shancai, you're doing great.

165
00:12:44,364 --> 00:12:45,444
Huaze Lei taught me well.

166
00:12:46,444 --> 00:12:47,844
She's a quick study.

167
00:12:50,164 --> 00:12:51,164
Please continue.

168
00:12:58,564 --> 00:13:00,484
I won't let you two win again.

169
00:13:01,204 --> 00:13:02,244
Says who?

170
00:13:02,684 --> 00:13:04,204
We might not lose.

171
00:13:05,764 --> 00:13:06,724
"We"?

172
00:13:07,844 --> 00:13:08,964
Shancai.

173
00:13:09,524 --> 00:13:11,324
The "we" that you and Huaze Lei refer to

174
00:13:11,404 --> 00:13:13,724
will soon disappear
from Mingde University.

175
00:13:25,084 --> 00:13:26,684
Why are they still not out?

176
00:13:26,884 --> 00:13:29,204
We finished the Big and Small game
in ten minutes.

177
00:13:29,284 --> 00:13:33,484
Qinghe, Shancai and Daoming Si
are playing an official game of Bridge.

178
00:13:34,044 --> 00:13:35,524
I know how to play that too.

179
00:13:35,604 --> 00:13:38,684
If I play them,
I'm sure F4 would surrender immediately.

180
00:13:38,844 --> 00:13:40,084
You silly boy.

181
00:13:40,164 --> 00:13:43,244
F4 is the champion of countless
international Bridge competitions.

182
00:13:44,004 --> 00:13:45,484
Whom do you think you're fooling?

183
00:13:46,004 --> 00:13:48,844
Qinghe, I know that you
and Shancai are close.

184
00:13:49,564 --> 00:13:51,964
But even so, you have to face reality.

185
00:13:53,044 --> 00:13:57,084
I think it would be better for you
to pray that she gets a nice set of cards.

186
00:13:57,644 --> 00:13:58,764
Xinhui, you're right.

187
00:14:00,684 --> 00:14:03,844
God, please protect the innocent
and cute Shancai.

188
00:14:03,924 --> 00:14:06,044
Don't let her be bullied
by the monster, Daoming Si.

189
00:14:08,124 --> 00:14:08,964
Shancai.

190
00:14:09,484 --> 00:14:10,484
You're bound to lose.

191
00:14:11,044 --> 00:14:13,324
No one has the trump suit now.

192
00:14:13,404 --> 00:14:16,484
And I'm now going to play
the Spade suit that you don't have.

193
00:14:17,404 --> 00:14:19,244
You'll surely lose this round.

194
00:14:35,244 --> 00:14:37,244
You didn't have the King of Spades?

195
00:14:43,804 --> 00:14:45,964
Shancai's King of Spades
beats Si's Queen of Spades.

196
00:14:46,524 --> 00:14:48,284
I thought we were bound to lose.

197
00:14:48,644 --> 00:14:50,524
Shancai, you're bound to lose, all right.

198
00:14:51,204 --> 00:14:52,564
Based on the cards played earlier,

199
00:14:52,644 --> 00:14:56,284
we all should have Diamonds
left in our hands.

200
00:14:56,844 --> 00:14:59,884
Si's card should be the highest among us.

201
00:15:00,444 --> 00:15:02,044
My memory can't be wrong,

202
00:15:02,324 --> 00:15:04,524
so you will lose this round.

203
00:15:05,524 --> 00:15:06,444
<i>Really?</i>

204
00:15:07,804 --> 00:15:10,364
<i>Are we really going to lose?</i>

205
00:15:13,164 --> 00:15:15,084
<i>Yes, that's the smile.</i>

206
00:15:15,764 --> 00:15:17,524
<i>That's the priceless smile.</i>

207
00:15:18,364 --> 00:15:19,684
<i>It gives me courage.</i>

208
00:15:20,244 --> 00:15:21,684
<i>I'm not afraid anymore.</i>

209
00:15:31,124 --> 00:15:33,084
Hey! Play your card!

210
00:15:51,244 --> 00:15:52,564
Si.

211
00:15:54,124 --> 00:15:55,364
Are you sure you'll win?

212
00:15:55,444 --> 00:15:56,284
We can't be too sure.

213
00:15:57,084 --> 00:15:58,764
Maybe he doesn't have any Diamonds.

214
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:02,564
If so, then we win.

215
00:16:03,044 --> 00:16:04,084
If we win,

216
00:16:04,164 --> 00:16:06,324
the one who'll leave
Mingde University is Daoming Si.

217
00:16:08,924 --> 00:16:10,284
In that case,

218
00:16:10,404 --> 00:16:11,964
maybe our stakes are too high.

219
00:16:12,324 --> 00:16:13,764
Because Si will surely win.

220
00:16:14,244 --> 00:16:18,724
Which means, the ones leaving
Mingde University will be Lei and Shancai.

221
00:16:18,804 --> 00:16:20,484
It's fine if we can't see Lei here.

222
00:16:20,644 --> 00:16:22,004
We can go to his house.

223
00:16:22,444 --> 00:16:23,804
If Shancai leaves,

224
00:16:24,044 --> 00:16:25,964
there will be no Ms. Flying Kick
at Mingde.

225
00:16:27,124 --> 00:16:28,044
That's fine.

226
00:16:28,124 --> 00:16:30,484
Then the school will no longer
have girls from average--

227
00:16:30,564 --> 00:16:33,044
Daoming Si. Are you playing or not?

228
00:16:33,604 --> 00:16:34,644
You're not scared, are you?

229
00:16:38,244 --> 00:16:39,484
Play your card.

230
00:16:41,404 --> 00:16:42,604
I'll acknowledge it if I lose.

231
00:17:14,084 --> 00:17:16,124
I'm not playing anymore! You guys suck.

232
00:17:26,524 --> 00:17:27,404
You won.

233
00:17:28,764 --> 00:17:30,084
We won?

234
00:17:31,444 --> 00:17:33,724
Huaze Lei, we won.

235
00:17:34,924 --> 00:17:36,084
Actually, we didn't win.

236
00:17:37,364 --> 00:17:38,284
Why not?

237
00:17:38,924 --> 00:17:41,044
Si couldn't beat my card.

238
00:17:41,124 --> 00:17:43,284
That's why he got mad
he mixed the cards up.

239
00:17:43,804 --> 00:17:45,124
What a sore loser.

240
00:17:45,884 --> 00:17:48,524
Si's card was actually higher
than all of ours.

241
00:17:49,164 --> 00:17:50,124
Meizuo.

242
00:17:52,084 --> 00:17:53,924
This was Si's card.

243
00:17:54,484 --> 00:17:56,364
My memory cannot be wrong.

244
00:17:59,084 --> 00:18:01,844
Nobody compares to Meizuo
in remembering cards.

245
00:18:05,804 --> 00:18:07,724
Then he won.

246
00:18:08,604 --> 00:18:10,124
Why did he stop playing?

247
00:18:13,284 --> 00:18:14,164
What do you think?

248
00:18:17,324 --> 00:18:20,084
Let's go. Ms. Zhuang is still waiting
to celebrate with us.

249
00:18:29,844 --> 00:18:30,684
<i>Come on.</i>

250
00:18:31,164 --> 00:18:32,844
<i>To all our good times together.</i>

251
00:18:32,924 --> 00:18:33,884
Cheers.

252
00:18:33,964 --> 00:18:35,324
Cheers.

253
00:18:39,924 --> 00:18:42,524
I think we were able to settle
the matter today, right?

254
00:18:42,604 --> 00:18:43,724
I hope so.

255
00:18:43,804 --> 00:18:46,084
But Si isn't home yet.

256
00:18:46,284 --> 00:18:48,164
I'm not sure where he went
after the competition.

257
00:18:49,004 --> 00:18:50,164
He'll be fine.

258
00:18:50,244 --> 00:18:54,284
Si used to quit in the middle
of playing Bridge before too.

259
00:18:54,364 --> 00:18:55,884
I know my brother very well.

260
00:18:55,964 --> 00:18:58,284
He's a self-centered, childish person.

261
00:18:59,484 --> 00:19:01,244
It's my fault.
I didn't discipline him well.

262
